# Lambda LAP — Windsurf Rules

## Project Context

Lambda LAP (SigmaLoop) is a full-stack educational platform for learning programming. Interactive code execution, course management, AI mentorship, and challenge-based grading.

## Repository Layout

- `Backend/` — Node.js + Express v5 + TypeScript REST API (MongoDB/Mongoose, JWT auth)
- `Frontend/` — React 19 + TypeScript + Vite SPA (Tailwind CSS, Monaco Editor)
- `Graduation Project/` — Design reference only (API contract, DB schema, UI mockups). Never modify for implementation.

## Architecture

- API at `http://localhost:4000/api/v1`, JSend response format
- SPA at `http://localhost:5173`, uses Axios with Bearer token interceptors
- MongoDB with Mongoose ODM, 9 collections
- JWT auth with 3 roles: STUDENT, INSTRUCTOR, ADMIN

## Key Patterns

### Backend (Express MVC)
- Entry: `Backend/src/server.ts` → `Backend/src/app.ts`
- Models: `src/models/` (Mongoose schemas with TypeScript interfaces)
- Controllers: `src/controllers/` (business logic, use JSend helpers for responses)
- Routes: `src/routes/` (registered in `routes/index.ts`)
- Auth: `src/middlewares/auth.middleware.ts` — `authenticate()` + `authorize(...roles)`
- Response helpers: `import { success, error } from '../utils/jsend'`

### Frontend (React SPA)
- Entry: `Frontend/src/main.tsx` → `Frontend/src/App.tsx`
- State: AuthContext (Context API) — `useAuth()` hook
- API: `src/services/api.ts` (Axios instance, auto-attaches JWT)
- Pages: `src/pages/` with layouts in `src/components/layouts/`
- UI primitives: `src/components/ui/` (Button, Card, Badge, Input)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS, custom `.glass-panel` / `.glass-card` classes

## Code Style

- Backend: ESLint Standard + TS, Prettier (single quotes, 100 chars)
- Frontend: ESLint recommended + TS, Prettier (double quotes, 80 chars)
- Both: strict TypeScript, Husky pre-commit hooks

## When Adding Features

1. Backend: Model → Controller → Route → Register in index.ts → Test
2. Frontend: Types in api.ts → Service function → Page component → Route in App.tsx
3. Always use existing patterns — JSend responses, auth middleware, Axios instance

